00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:26,740
 There's several other places where we can find

270
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:28,580
 a list of spiritual gifts, right.

271
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:30,340
 This is not an exhaustive list,

272
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,860
 and we don't have time to go through each and every single

273
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:35,860
 of these ones specifically today,

274
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:38,300
 but there are a couple of things I want us to notice

275
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:40,420
 as we look through things like this.

276
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,840
 Firstly is this, they are given to us,

277
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:46,040
 they are given to us through the Spirit.

278
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:51,520
 You don't earn these gifts by being extra super holy, right.

279
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:54,260
 You can't buy them with money.

280
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:57,260
 These gifts are God's way of working through us,

281
00:11:57,260 --> 00:11:59,660
 equipping us, encouraging us,

282
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:03,900
 using us for the sake of His kingdom and His glory.

283
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:06,660
 Right, they are God's idea.

284
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:11,660
 They are a blessing from God, and God loves giving us gifts.

285
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:13,300
 Bible tells us specifically that God

286
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:16,060
 is the best giver of gifts,

287
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:18,940
 and that every good and perfect gift

288
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:22,380
 comes from our loving Father in Heaven.

289
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:26,140
 So they're given to us, it's a gift, we don't earn it.

290
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:29,280
 And also as you see, there are many of them.

291
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:32,160
 It's a long list, and like I said, it's not the only list.

292
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:35,620
 There's a variety of gifts and functions,

293
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:39,180
 and that's a good thing, that's the beautiful thing.

294
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:42,320
 So therefore, your gift in the Holy Spirit,

295
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:44,760
 it's not your supernatural, not your superpower

296
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:47,140
 made for everybody to look at you.

297
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:52,140
 Your gift is your part in the body of Christ.

298
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:55,340
 This means that unless you're using your gift

299
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:58,340
 to serve the Lord, to serve the community of Christ,

300
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:00,940
 to serve the body of Christ,

301
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:05,640
 the church cannot be all that God meant for it to be.

302
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:10,060
 Paul will say it like this in Romans 12.

303
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:13,700
 For just as each of us has one body with many members,

304
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,860
 and these members do not all have the same function,

305
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:20,300
 so in Christ, though many, form one body,

306
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,780
 and each member belongs to the others.

307
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:26,640
 We have different gifts according to the grace given to us.

308
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:29,420
 If your gift is prophesying,

309
00:13:29,420 --> 00:13:32,160
 then prophesy in accordance with your faith.

310
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,700
 If it's serving, then serve.

311
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:35,140
 If it's teaching, then teach.

312
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:37,380
 If it's to encourage, then give encouragement.

313
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:39,420
 If it's giving, then give generously.

314
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:41,740
 If it's to lead, do it diligently.

315
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:44,600
 If it's to show mercy, do it cheerfully.

316
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,940
 Everybody needs to pitch in

317
00:13:48,940 --> 00:13:52,460
 because every single person in this room,

318
00:13:52,460 --> 00:13:55,020
 the Bible tells us, has a gift,

319
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:58,060
 and therefore you have a role to play.

320
00:13:58,060 --> 00:14:00,760
 Again, this is important to keep in mind

321
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,220
 because the danger is,

322
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:04,740
 especially when it comes to spiritual gifts,

323
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:08,420
 we start to see some gifts as better than the others,

324
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,620
 which means that some people think

325
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,900
 that they're more important than they actually are,

326
00:14:11,900 --> 00:14:13,540
 and some people end up thinking

327
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:16,380
 they underestimate the crucial part

328
00:14:16,380 --> 00:14:18,840
 that they are to play in God's kingdom.

329
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:22,260
 So for example, what's happening right here,

330
00:14:22,260 --> 00:14:25,060
 people being on the stage, speaking, teaching,

331
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:27,140
 singing, whatever it is,

332
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,780
 to people all throughout the day,

333
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:30,740
 this is a gift that's often lifted up

334
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:32,880
 and seen as highly important.

335
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:36,020
 But what about the gift of serving?

