00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:39,300
 What about the people that held the signs

337
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:41,100
 that served you by greeting you

338
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,340
 on the way up to the auditorium this morning?

339
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:45,460
 What about the team of hosts

340
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:48,620
 that passed from the offering buckets just now?

341
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:50,580
 What about the communion we're about to take later

342
00:14:50,580 --> 00:14:53,300
 that people had to come in at 7 a.m. this morning

343
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,780
 to tear up the pieces of bread,

344
00:14:54,780 --> 00:14:56,100
 to fill up the little cups,

345
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,580
 just so that we can have communion later?

346
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:02,040
 Did it cross your mind that our greeters

347
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:05,820
 and hosts and volunteers play just as critical a part

348
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:07,940
 in the body of Christ than the preacher

349
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:10,620
 or the worship team when it comes to our Sunday services?

350
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:13,460
 And I'm just talking about Sunday services here.

351
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:16,260
 Without people who are willing to use the gifts

352
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:17,740
 of serving the church,

353
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:20,340
 none of this would be possible, guys, none.

354
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:22,860
 There would be no production team,

355
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,340
 the band would be one or two people,

356
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,340
 there would be no kids and youth ministry,

357
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:29,020
 this whole place would be in chaos.

358
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:32,860
 But God, in His infinite wisdom,

359
00:15:32,860 --> 00:15:34,980
 in His perfect knowledge of His children,

360
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:38,340
 in His generosity, He looks at a group like us,

361
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:40,380
 and then through the Holy Spirit,

362
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:43,700
 He distributes gifts and expects everyone

363
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:47,000
 to use their gifts and play their part,

364
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:50,860
 so that the whole church can function healthily.

365
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:53,620
 This is what He's talking about.

366
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:55,620
 Again, let's go back to Scripture.

367
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:57,660
 God has put the body together

368
00:15:57,660 --> 00:16:01,940
 so that there should be no division in the body,

369
00:16:01,940 --> 00:16:06,180
 but all the parts have equal concern for each other.

370
00:16:06,180 --> 00:16:09,440
 If one part suffers, every part suffers with it.

371
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:13,620
 If one part is honored, every part rejoices with it.

372
00:16:13,620 --> 00:16:16,500
 You see, from a worldly perspective,

373
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:20,180
 when we get gifts, when we give gifts or get gifts,

374
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:22,100
 it is something quite personal,

375
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,940
 and you get it with that person in mind.

376
00:16:23,940 --> 00:16:25,660
 Well, hopefully you spare some thought,

377
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,420
 that's a nice thing to do,

378
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:29,300
 to think about that person and get them a gift,

379
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,680
 birthday, anniversaries, graduations.

380
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:33,540
 You think about the need

381
00:16:33,540 --> 00:16:36,140
 and you get something tailored for that person.

382
00:16:36,140 --> 00:16:38,300
 And then when that person receives a gift,

383
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:40,860
 there is no expectation to share it.

384
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:42,060
 I mean, you wouldn't get, you know,

385
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:44,360
 if I bought Nathan a new pair of shoes,

386
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,200
 I would say something like,

387
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,640
 "Okay, hey, you know, those new Jordans are pretty cool,

388
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:48,820
 "but you have to let me wear them

389
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,580
 "on Mondays and Wednesdays, okay?"

390
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:52,000
 Apart from the fact they wouldn't fit,

391
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,720
 it doesn't make sense, that's not how gifts work.

392
00:16:54,720 --> 00:17:00,220
 But when it comes to spiritual gifts,

393
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:02,820
 the perspective is different.

394
00:17:02,820 --> 00:17:05,940
 So yes, the personal element is still there.

395
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:08,860
 Again, not everyone has the same gift,

396
00:17:08,860 --> 00:17:12,540
 which means when God looks at you as his child,

397
00:17:12,540 --> 00:17:15,700
 as the person who he knitted together in his mother's womb,

398
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,620
 your God who knows the amount of hairs on your head,

399
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:21,700
 he saw you and he gave you a gift specifically

400
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:24,460
 through the Holy Spirit with you in mind,

401
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:27,620
 with his wisdom, with his love, with his grace.

402
00:17:27,620 --> 00:17:29,500
 And when we receive this gift from God, right,

403
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,900
 there is a sense of closeness and intimacy

404
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,740
 that we feel with the Father

405
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:36,240
 and he draws us closer to him.

406
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:39,740
 The thing is, after we receive that,

407
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:42,260
 they are then meant to be shared.

408
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:44,540
 These gifts are designed for us to use

409
00:17:44,540 --> 00:17:47,220
 to help those around us.

410
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:50,620
 For example, healing is a gift.

411
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,100
 But I mean, there's only so much healing

412
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,300
 you can do on yourself, right?

413
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,580
 And then God gives you the gift of healing

414
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:59,360
 so that you can have mercy to those around you

415
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:01,100
 who are in need.

416
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,780
 He gives you the gift of faith

417
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:04,780
 so that when you see someone struggling

418
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:07,020
 in their season of life, you can come alongside them,

419
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:09,460
 say, I will pray with you, I will walk with you,

420
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,780
 let's do this together.

421
00:18:10,780 --> 00:18:12,460
 That's the gift of faith.

422
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:17,340
 All these gifts that we get only make sense

423
00:18:17,340 --> 00:18:19,920
 when they're shared amongst the church.

424
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:23,620
 So if you find yourself with these gifts,

425
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:26,020
 the question we should be asking ourselves is not,

426
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:28,740
 how is this gift gonna benefit me?

427
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:31,340
 That's worldly, fleshly thinking.

428
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:33,780
 That's a mistake that dude made when he said to Peter,

429
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:36,740
 and if he could buy the gift that he saw Peter had

430
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:39,740
 with money, but what was his response?

431
00:18:39,740 --> 00:18:42,180
 May your money perish with you

432
00:18:42,180 --> 00:18:45,560
 because you thought you could buy the gift of God with money.

433
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:49,700
 You have no part or share in this ministry

434
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:53,380
 because your heart is not right before God.

435
00:18:53,380 --> 00:18:57,020
 So let me remind us again,

436
00:18:57,060 --> 00:19:01,740
 these gifts of the Spirit are given for the common good.

437
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:03,880
 You see what I'm beginning,

438
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,120
 you understand what I'm saying now?

439
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:07,260
 That it's not about you.

440
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:10,020
 It's not for one person to stand out at the star,

441
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:12,140
 but these gifts are given to us to highlight

442
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:16,060
 just how much God wants us to serve

443
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:18,620
 and to need each other.

444
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:22,820
 So this presents a question and a challenge to all of us.

445
00:19:22,820 --> 00:19:25,900
 What is our gift?

446
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:27,220
 And once you discover your gift,

447
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:30,540
 how are you using it to serve the body of Christ,

448
00:19:30,540 --> 00:19:32,840
 to serve the Lord, to serve the church?

449
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:37,860
 Because like I said, everyone has a role to play,

450
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:39,260
 and I'll just say it plainly,

451
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:42,580
 showing up on a Sunday is not a spiritual gift.

452
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:45,340
 Right?

453
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:46,180
 It's not.

454
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:49,300
 But do you know your part?

455
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,380
 Are you playing your part?

