 Like you think you have this talent and your gift to sing,

524
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,920
 but actually that's not your gift.

525
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:05,000
 And somewhere along the way, there've been disillusion

526
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,400
 or someone has lied to them.

527
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,860
 You know, maybe they sang in front of their mom

528
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:10,240
 and the mom's like, oh yeah, yeah, you're really good.

529
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:11,840
 You're good at everything, son, okay?

530
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:14,600
 And you go off, yeah, go do the audition.

531
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:18,120
 And you find out, actually, that's not what you're good at.

532
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:23,040
 In the same way, right, the Bible does say ask,

533
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:26,400
 earnestly ask and desire the gifts.

534
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,880
 But it also tells us that everything must be done

535
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:33,080
 so that the church may be built up.

536
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:37,520
 So whatever the Holy Spirit has decided to bless you with,

537
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:40,440
 trust Him with that, lean into that.

538
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:43,020
 Again, I'm not saying you can't ask, you can't desire,

539
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:45,780
 do those things, the Holy Spirit might choose to work in you

540
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:47,240
 in that way at some time.

541
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:51,980
 But whatever God has given to you, trust Him with that,

542
00:23:51,980 --> 00:23:55,500
 lean into that and serve and work out of that

543
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,620
 so that when the Spirit is at work in your life,

544
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:02,940
 He can give you the gift to serve the body of Christ.

545
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:07,460
 Now that's a gift of the Spirit, the gifts of the Spirit.

546
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:10,580
 But the Spirit at work in your life

547
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:14,060
 should also grow fruit within you.

548
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:14,900
 Well, what's the difference?

549
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:17,420
 Well, I would say probably that you can look at it like this.

550
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:22,420
 Gifts are normally for certain times and certain seasons

551
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:24,260
 and certain moments.

552
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:26,580
 For example, tongues, again, is described

553
00:24:26,580 --> 00:24:28,700
 as one of the spiritual gifts.

554
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,060
 Every now and then, in the worship service at the Vine,

555
00:24:31,060 --> 00:24:34,440
 we'll have a gift of tongues and there'll be interpretation

556
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:37,940
 and the whole church is strengthened and edified

557
00:24:37,940 --> 00:24:40,380
 by the gift of tongues.

558
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:43,580
 But if that were to happen constantly, every day,

559
00:24:43,580 --> 00:24:45,820
 all the time, we wouldn't be able to get on

560
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:47,420
 to anything else.

561
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:51,780
 Healing, again, is certain gifts for certain moments.

562
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:54,100
 Every now and then, we get called to pray

563
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:57,460
 for those who are sick and we see healing take place.

564
00:24:57,460 --> 00:25:00,220
 We've seen some very powerful ways the Holy Spirit

565
00:25:00,220 --> 00:25:04,220
 has worked and healed people from all sorts of things.

566
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:07,900
 But again, there's a certain time and place for that.

567
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:10,940
 That's not to mean that the Holy Spirit can't heal

568
00:25:10,940 --> 00:25:12,220
 when we pray.

569
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:15,100
 It just means that the Holy Spirit is choosing not to act

570
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:18,320
 in that way for that particular moment.

571
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:23,880
 But when it comes to the fruit, the fruit isn't something

572
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,960
 that we see every now and then.

573
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:29,060
 The fruit of the Spirit is something we constantly

574
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:30,680
 need to be growing in.

575
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:35,860
 This is why Paul says, "Walk by the Spirit."

576
00:25:35,860 --> 00:25:38,260
 The word walk here isn't talking about like a stroll

577
00:25:38,260 --> 00:25:41,020
 down the beach or a stroll in the park.

578
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:44,620
 It's talking about how you live your life,

579
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:46,780
 the choices you make.

580
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:49,740
 And we need to be really careful about this

581
00:25:49,740 --> 00:25:52,560
 because again, the consequences are serious.

582
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:56,380
 Galatians 5, check out what Paul has to say.

583
00:25:56,380 --> 00:26:00,060
 Walk by the Spirit and you will not gratify the desires

584
00:26:00,060 --> 00:26:01,500
 of the flesh.

585
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:04,140
 For the flesh desires what is contrary to the Spirit

586
00:26:04,140 --> 00:26:07,020
 and the Spirit what is contrary to the flesh.

587
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:10,900
 They are in conflict with each other so that you are not

588
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:13,820
 to do whatever you want.

589
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:20,800
 Walk by the Spirit and you will not gratify the desires

590
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,500
 of the flesh.

591
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:26,180
 It's very clear, Paul's very clear, Scripture's very clear.

592
00:26:26,180 --> 00:26:27,860
 We felt this too.

593
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:31,060
 There's a constant battle going on inside of us,

594
00:26:31,060 --> 00:26:33,700
 outside of us between what the flesh wants

595
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:37,340
 and what the Spirit is trying to lead us towards.

596
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:38,900
 And here's the thing, right?

597
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:42,000
 The Bible tells us we can't just do whatever we want

598
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,420
 and call it freedom.

599
00:26:43,420 --> 00:26:47,760
 It's a bit sort of contradictory because if we're being told

600
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:50,780
 how to live, right, on one level that sounds more

601
00:26:50,780 --> 00:26:53,200
 like a restriction rather than freedom.

602
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:56,940
 But what does freedom in this case actually look like?

603
00:26:56,940 --> 00:27:00,660
 What does freedom in Christ actually look like?

604
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:02,180
 'Cause we talk about freedom a lot.

605
00:27:02,180 --> 00:27:04,340
 But one of the great benefits of Christianity

606
00:27:04,340 --> 00:27:06,860
 and the life in Jesus is freedom.

607
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:09,200
 Again, we sing about it, we preach about it,

608
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:11,780
 we proclaim Bible verses about freedom.

609
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:15,140
 Who the Son sets free is free indeed, yes, and amen.

610
00:27:15,140 --> 00:27:17,940
 But what are we talking about when we talk about freedom?

611
00:27:17,940 --> 00:27:21,500
 Well, from the worldly, fleshly perspective,

612
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:25,140
 freedom is the ability to say and think and do

613
00:27:25,140 --> 00:27:27,980
 and act whatever you like, right?

614
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:30,940
 A life with no limits and no control.

615
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:32,980
 This is how kids think, right?

616
00:27:32,980 --> 00:27:35,140
 Kids look up to us, our children look up to us,

617
00:27:35,140 --> 00:27:37,140
 and they think, oh, I can't wait 'til I'm an adult

618
00:27:37,140 --> 00:27:38,940
 so I can eat ice cream all day,

619
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:41,580
 I can melt my brain with TV, you know,

620
00:27:41,580 --> 00:27:44,500
 and I can just buy any toy I want anytime I want, right?

621
00:27:44,500 --> 00:27:47,300
 That is how a kid looks at us, right, and see,

622
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:50,380
 well, freedom is to be able to do whatever we want

623
00:27:50,380 --> 00:27:51,560
 anytime we want.

624
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:55,900
 But even as adults, right, we tend to look at freedom

625
00:27:55,900 --> 00:27:56,780
 in this way.

626
00:27:58,140 --> 00:28:01,900
 A life of freedom is if, well, I can live on my own terms.

627
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:04,140
 Right, isn't that what the world approves of?

628
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,360
 You deserve it.

629
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:08,540
 Live life on your own terms, do whatever you want,

630
00:28:08,540 --> 00:28:10,740
 be free, don't let anybody hold you down.

631
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:13,580
 You only live once, right, so come on, just go for it.

632
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:15,380
 Do it, doesn't matter.

633
00:28:15,380 --> 00:28:19,380
 Now, life this way might sound appealing.

634
00:28:19,380 --> 00:28:23,460
 The only problem is God's Word tells us

635
00:28:23,460 --> 00:28:24,860
 something quite different.

636
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:28,940
 And Scripture warns us that freedom in the flesh

637
00:28:28,940 --> 00:28:31,740
 will lead us to some dark places,

638
00:28:31,740 --> 00:28:35,380
 places filled with things like sexual immorality,

639
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:39,900
 impurity and debauchery, idolatry, witchcraft,

640
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:44,060
 hatred, discord, jealousy, fits of rage,

641
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:47,120
 selfish ambition, dissensions, factions,

642
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:50,340
 and envy, drunkenness, orgies, and the like.

643
00:28:50,340 --> 00:28:54,160
 I warn you, as I did before, that those who live like this

644
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:57,380
 will not inherit the kingdom of God.

645
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:59,880
 When you read through that list,

646
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:02,400
 you know what it sounds like to me?

647
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:05,080
 It sounds like chaos and disorder.

648
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:08,860
 Right, that sounds like everyone out for themselves,

649
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:11,060
 not caring about those around them.

650
00:29:11,060 --> 00:29:16,740
 That list sounds like darkness and hatred and evil.

651
00:29:16,740 --> 00:29:18,600
 It's the road to destruction

652
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:21,760
 and eternal separation from God.

653
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:25,560
 Freedom in the flesh is not true freedom.

654
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:31,260
 Firstly, it goes against who you were created to be.

655
00:29:31,260 --> 00:29:34,380
 Right, because you were created to be a human being

656
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:37,740
 that glorifies himself or herself.

657
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:42,220
 You were created to be an image bearer of God.

658
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:45,660
 This means that you feel your sense and your purpose,

659
00:29:45,660 --> 00:29:48,080
 not when you're out doing whatever you want,

660
00:29:48,080 --> 00:29:51,340
 but when your life is fully obedient

661
00:29:51,340 --> 00:29:53,700
 to what Jesus has called you to.

662
00:29:53,700 --> 00:29:55,500
 That is when you feel most alive.

663
00:29:55,500 --> 00:29:57,420
 That is when you're gonna feel most free.

664
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:59,700
 That is when you're gonna realize what your purpose,

665
00:29:59,700 --> 00:30:03,000
 your destiny, whatever word you want to use in life is.

666
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:09,020
 Second thing is this, you end up in a terrible place.

667
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:12,620
 Paul says it clearly, that those who live like this

668
00:30:12,620 --> 00:30:14,940
 will not inherit the kingdom of God.

669
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:17,500
 You will have no part in what God's trying to do

670
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:20,620
 in this life or the next.

671
00:30:20,620 --> 00:30:24,300
 In other words, you are separated from God now

672
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:26,320
 and for all eternity.

673
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:31,500
 And free living that leads to chaos and separation from God

674
00:30:31,500 --> 00:30:33,660
 is not freedom at all.

675
00:30:33,660 --> 00:30:37,060
 Remember what Pastor Andrew said

676
00:30:37,060 --> 00:30:38,820
 at the beginning of this series?

677
00:30:38,820 --> 00:30:43,120
 That the Holy Spirit is what brings order out of chaos.

678
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:45,980
 And this is what he wants to do

679
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:48,540
 in the body of Christ in our lives.

680
00:30:48,540 --> 00:30:49,860
 And Paul is about to give us

681
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:52,620
 one of the most beautiful examples

682
00:30:52,620 --> 00:30:55,980
 of what a life of order in the Holy Spirit looks like.

683
00:30:55,980 --> 00:30:58,860
 I would say that this is one of the most beautiful pictures

684
00:30:58,860 --> 00:31:02,340
 of order and of peace and of the way God wants us to live

685
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:04,260
 outside of Genesis 1.

686
00:31:04,260 --> 00:31:06,700
 Genesis 1, we have Eden and it's perfect.

687
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:10,940
 This is an echo of what God has talked to us about

688
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:11,780
 in Genesis 1.

689
00:31:11,780 --> 00:31:13,240
 Listen to what the Bible says.

690
00:31:14,340 --> 00:31:19,340
 But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace,

691
00:31:19,340 --> 00:31:23,860
 patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,

692
00:31:23,860 --> 00:31:26,140
 gentleness, and self-control.

693
00:31:26,140 --> 00:31:30,340
 Against such things there is no law.

694
00:31:30,340 --> 00:31:35,460
 Doesn't this sound a lot more like peace and order?

695
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:40,460
 Doesn't this sound like the things we want to chase in life?

696
00:31:40,460 --> 00:31:43,660
 Isn't this what you hope you've been created for?

697
00:31:44,580 --> 00:31:48,340
 Now, there is an important detail to note.

698
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:52,060
 And this is important because this verse is so well known.

699
00:31:52,060 --> 00:31:54,420
 Sometimes as Christians when it comes to this,

700
00:31:54,420 --> 00:31:57,740
 we like to do like a little stock index exchange

701
00:31:57,740 --> 00:31:59,020
 on this passage.

702
00:31:59,020 --> 00:31:59,980
 And we begin to think like,

703
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:02,500
 oh well, I wasn't very kind today,

704
00:32:02,500 --> 00:32:04,460
 but I did have peace about it.

705
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:08,100
 Or, well, I didn't so much self-control,

706
00:32:08,100 --> 00:32:10,280
 but there was a lot of joy.

707
00:32:12,380 --> 00:32:13,860
 Don't do this, okay?

708
00:32:13,860 --> 00:32:15,420
 Doesn't make sense.

709
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:18,220
 The fruit of the Spirit is not your stock portfolio.

710
00:32:18,220 --> 00:32:21,500
 If you have lots of gains in one,

711
00:32:21,500 --> 00:32:23,420
 it doesn't cover the losses in the other.

712
00:32:23,420 --> 00:32:25,060
 Do you know what I'm saying?

713
00:32:25,060 --> 00:32:28,740
 Can you really be faithful without being patient?

714
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:31,900
 Is there real joy without having peace?

715
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:35,220
 There's a simple thing, you might already know this,

716
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:36,180
 I'm gonna remind us.

717
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:38,980
 It's not the fruits of the Spirit,

718
00:32:38,980 --> 00:32:43,980
 it's the fruit, singular, of the Spirit.

719
00:32:43,980 --> 00:32:45,340
 If you've not heard that before,

720
00:32:45,340 --> 00:32:47,020
 write it down in your margins, okay?

721
00:32:47,020 --> 00:32:50,700
 The fruit of the Spirit.

722
00:32:50,700 --> 00:32:53,140
 And if we're gonna grow in the fruit,

723
00:32:53,140 --> 00:32:54,620
 if we're gonna walk by the Spirit,

724
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:56,900
 then we're gonna have to dedicate

725
00:32:56,900 --> 00:33:00,920
 every part of ourselves in this journey.

726
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:03,940
 And again, it's not an easy one.

727
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:07,740
 The true Christian life,

728
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:11,260
 if we're really to follow Jesus with everything we have,

729
00:33:11,260 --> 00:33:13,360
 it's not the easy path to choose.

730
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:15,900
 It's the narrow path.

731
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:19,460
 Because like we said, your spirit and your flesh

732
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:22,900
 are constantly gonna be at conflict with each other.

733
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:24,660
 There isn't a version of following Jesus

734
00:33:24,660 --> 00:33:27,560
 where we just get to coast and sail off into the sunset,

735
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:30,500
 not giving a thought to how we're actually supposed

736
00:33:30,500 --> 00:33:32,160
 to live our lives.

737
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:35,660
 No, but it's a life of discipline.

738
00:33:35,660 --> 00:33:40,020
 Paul calls it, it's a training up for godliness.

739
00:33:40,020 --> 00:33:42,700
 Fruit takes time and effort to grow, right?

740
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:45,100
 You can't just plonk a tree in some soil

741
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:47,020
 and just expect it to do its thing.

742
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:49,520
 It takes nurturing, it takes watering,

743
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:51,580
 it takes nutrients, it takes protection

744
00:33:51,580 --> 00:33:53,340
 from the elements and other insects,

745
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:56,420
 it takes pruning and grafting and all that kind of stuff.

746
00:33:56,420 --> 00:33:58,400
 It just doesn't happen automatically.

747
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:02,140
 Which is why, in your Christian life,

748
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:04,980
 it's always gonna be about choosing God's way

749
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,700
 instead of your way.

750
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:11,260
 Your old self, with its attraction to chaos and sin,

751
00:34:11,260 --> 00:34:13,580
 full of passion and the desires of the flesh,

752
00:34:13,580 --> 00:34:15,380
 is always gonna try and draw you back

753
00:34:15,380 --> 00:34:17,140
 to that place of chaos.

754
00:34:17,140 --> 00:34:20,860
 The enemy and the devil and its minions

755
00:34:20,860 --> 00:34:22,740
 and the enemy of this world is always trying

756
00:34:22,740 --> 00:34:26,200
 to use temptation to draw you back into that place

757
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:28,740
 of separation from God, of living life

758
00:34:28,740 --> 00:34:31,540
 without the Holy Spirit.

759
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:34,320
 This is why we've been saying,

760
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:39,160
 we need to deal with sin seriously.

761
00:34:39,160 --> 00:34:41,480
 And when we made the decision to follow Jesus,

762
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:45,200
 it means also identifying with him in death,

763
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:47,080
 which means that our sinful desires,

764
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:48,560
 the thing we used to follow in this world,

765
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:51,960
 have been crucified to the cross with Jesus.

766
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:54,920
 There is no space for that in our walk

767
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:56,440
 with the Holy Spirit now.

768
00:34:56,440 --> 00:35:00,960
 Okay, again, take a deep breath,

769
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,960
 'cause it sounds like a lot of pressure.

770
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:07,520
 The good news is that you don't,

771
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:11,320
 or even you cannot do this by your own power.

772
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:14,480
 And that's good news.

773
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:19,480
 And just as the gifts are from the Holy Spirit,

774
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:23,440
 the ability to put your flesh to death,

775
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:26,560
 to grow in the fruit, to walk with the Spirit,

776
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:29,360
 that is also something that the Holy Spirit

777
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:31,140
 has to empower you in.

778
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:35,120
 Right, it's repeated multiple times in this passage.

779
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:38,360
 We need to be led by the Spirit.

780
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,640
 We need to walk by the Spirit.

781
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,120
 We need to live by the Spirit.

782
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:43,920
 We need to keep in step with the Spirit.

783
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,960
 The Spirit is there to guide, to lead, to hold,

784
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:49,560
 to draw you back, to push you forward,

785
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:53,320
 to help you live this Christian life.

786
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:56,000
 And just like we rely on the Holy Spirit

787
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:58,120
 to give us our spiritual gifts,

788
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:00,540
 in the same way, the Holy Spirit helps us

789
00:36:00,540 --> 00:36:03,600
 to live lives that will bear fruit.

790
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:10,720
 Now again, this is not self-help, okay?

791
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:13,540
 This isn't about making yourself a better person,

792
00:36:13,540 --> 00:36:16,760
 self-improvement, it's not about becoming more virtuous

793
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:19,040
 so people can look at you a certain way.

794
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:21,200
 This is about dealing with your sin

795
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:23,520
 so that you can have a living, working,

796
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:27,680
 convicting, obedient, life, eternity-changing

797
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:30,400
 relationship with Jesus.

798
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:33,700
 And He is the one who helps you through it.

799
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:37,300
 Remain in me, He says, as I also remain in you.

800
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:39,380
 No branch can bear fruit by itself,

801
00:36:39,380 --> 00:36:40,860
 it must remain in the vine,

802
00:36:40,860 --> 00:36:45,660
 neither can you bear fruit unless you remain in me.

803
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:50,780
 A life totally reliant and connected to our Savior,

804
00:36:50,780 --> 00:36:52,720
 to the Holy, and to the Holy Spirit.

805
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:57,140
 This is what true freedom looks like.

806
00:36:59,060 --> 00:37:04,060
 And when we live this way, it tells us there is no law.

807
00:37:04,060 --> 00:37:07,940
 God's never gonna stop you from growing

808
00:37:07,940 --> 00:37:09,220
 in the fruit of the Spirit.

809
00:37:09,220 --> 00:37:11,220
 No government or authority is ever gonna say,

810
00:37:11,220 --> 00:37:12,660
 stop doing these things, right?

811
00:37:12,660 --> 00:37:16,700
 These are good, virtuous, amazing things, right?

812
00:37:16,700 --> 00:37:19,700
 Nothing will ever stop you from growing in the Spirit.

813
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:21,880
 There is no law against these things.

814
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:25,420
 And so once you've had the fruit,

815
00:37:25,420 --> 00:37:28,540
 you've tasted and seen that the fruit

816
00:37:28,540 --> 00:37:31,880
 of the Spirit is good, you will begin living

817
00:37:31,880 --> 00:37:34,140
 in a way that brings true life

818
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:38,860
 to yourself and to those around you.

819
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:41,180
 And as difficult as it may be at time,

820
00:37:41,180 --> 00:37:43,820
 you will never want to stop growing in them.

821
00:37:43,820 --> 00:37:50,840
 The gifts and the fruit, therefore, go hand in hand.

822
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:57,000
 You are being called to build up the kingdom of God

823
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,600
 here on earth as it is in heaven.

824
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:03,960
 But you're also being called to live lives of holiness

825
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:08,960
 and closeness that reflect God's heart and who he is.

826
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:12,400
 And God expects both his followers

827
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:16,480
 to use their gifts and to bear fruit.

828
